  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Anyway, I do know from my father that he was-- that he was enlisted then to provide medical help to-- in case of some injuries to the Polish-- I mean, to the Jewish porters hit by the Poles.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I don't think it came, actually, to any kind of real serious loss of life or, or serious injuries.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But it was going on, and I as a kid was already aware.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Anyway we are now in 1940 in Rowne, East Poland.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And some time around that time, maybe 1940, the Russians put the trains on the-- on the railroad station.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we knew that they are going to make searches house to house and pick up people that cross the border illegally or whatever and ship them at night to Siberia.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I think that somebody tipped off my father because he had special papers saying that he's, as a physician, indispensable in town.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They came to our apartment in the middle of the night at, at 2:00 or so and told us [RUSSIAN], which means pick, pick up your belongings, and we're going to ship you into Siberia, to the Russian paradise.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] then I remember that scene, and my uncle, incidentally, and my cousin were hidden in the attic-- my uncle, Shimon, and my cousin, Jerrzyk.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so when they-- when the guy came to ship us, my father showed him the papers and they relented, and that was the end of that.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, I am coming to June 22, '41 when Germans invaded Russia, and the war broke out.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For some crazy reason, because I had crooked teeth, my, my, my parents sent me with my sister to my aunt that lived at that's time in Lwow for some tooth correction or whatever.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
